<HEADLINE>
FT  14 APR 94 / Teleworking gains popularity slowly
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Teleworking - working from home using computing or telecommunications
equipment - remains a minority activity but is gaining in popularity,
Incomes Data Services, the pay and employment analysts, said.
In a report IDS said that the consensus view is that between 5 per cent and
15 per cent of organisations employ staff who spend at least half of their
working time at home.
</TEXT>
